# Build output
src/**/bin/
src/**/obj/

# Download cache for externally hosted files (the WDM MPQ patches). Only ever used to
# compute hashes at manifest time - players fetch these from upstream, not from here.
.external-cache/

# Local launcher config - each install writes its own next to the exe
uncapped.config.json

# The crash-report Discord webhook, baked into the binary at build time.
# Deliberately NOT committed: this repo is public, and a webhook URL sitting in
# public source is findable through GitHub code search in seconds and is actively
# scraped. In the shipped binary it still costs someone a deliberate look with
# `strings`, which is a materially different bar.
# Rotating it means editing this file and cutting a release. To kill it without a
# release, set "crashReportWebhook" in manifest.json to any non-empty value that
# is not a URL, or empty to fall back to this baked-in one.
src/Uncapped/webhook.local.txt

# payload/ and manifest.json are generated but MUST be committed:
# they are what the launcher actually downloads.

# Internal planning notes. This repo is public: the handoff contains server-side detail and
# a written record of the client-distribution decision, neither of which needs publishing.
# Delete this line if you want it in the repo.
HANDOFF_LAUNCHER.md
